				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Bondocones" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The game is played on what is roughly a checker board with 10x12 squares. Each player has 26 cones with a value of either zero (10), 1 (5), 2 (6), 4 (4) or 8 (1) and each turn you can move one cone according to a roll of a die. You try to capture your opponents cones by landing on them, but since the value of each cone is hidden from you opponent you never quite know what you get. The game ends when one player has 28 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When moving you can only move in a straight line either horizontally, diagonally or vertically. The exception is one of your cones which has a red ring placed around it - the so called &amp;quot;bondocone.&amp;quot; With this you can move in any direction, but may not step on the same square twice. You can capture your opponents &amp;quot;bondo&amp;quot; and thus have two bondocones.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is in it's current version also a piece of designer furniture made specific to fit into trendy caf&amp;eacute;s or as home interior design. The materials are exclusive and really adds to a great gaming experience... Nothing beats a quality game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
